The *image.tag* parameter can be used to specify a different image for the chart, as described in the [documentation for using a different image version](../configuration/change-image-version/).

When specifying the *image.tag* parameter to use an image from a private registry, it is necessary to also [specify an image pull secret](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/containers/images/#specifying-imagepullsecrets-on-a-pod), as described below:

* Manually create image pull secret(s) in the namespace. Use this [YAML example reference](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/containers/images/#creating-a-secret-with-a-docker-config) to ceate the image pull secret and consult your image registry's documentation about getting the appropriate secret.

* Pass the secret to the chart using the *imagePullSecrets* parameter. Note that this configuration value cannot currently be passed to Helm using the *--set* parameter and must be supplied via a *values.yaml* file, as shown below. Replace the SECRET-NAME placeholder with the correct name of the configured image pull secret.

  ```yaml
  imagePullSecrets:
    - name: SECRET-NAME
  ```

* Install the chart as usual.
